Package: totalize
Title: Aggregate Values By Groups And Make Their Total
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Ichiro", "Murata", , "ichiro21.murata@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
    )
Description:  To count or aggregate values by groups can be done by ordinary R methods, while 'totalize' makes their total additionaly.
    It is useful especially when grouping data by 2 or more variables combination.
    The return value is provided in arranged matrix representation.
